Key Match Events: Denver Nuggets defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 126-103 on January 8, 2025.
Jamal Murray led the Nuggets with 21 points on 13 shots and nine assists against two turnovers.
Russell Westbrook added 19 points on 16 shots with eight assists versus three turnovers.
DeAndre Jordan made his first start of the season in place of Nikola Jokic, who missed the game due to illness.
Post-Match Reflections: Jamal Murray expressed his joy about spending time on the court with his young daughter before the game.
Russell Westbrook commented on his growing on-court chemistry with Jamal Murray, highlighting Murray's ability to catch and shoot and play off the ball.
Jamal Murray discussed the different approaches he takes when playing pick-and-rolls with DeAndre Jordan compared to Nikola Jokic.
